    },
    {
      "$component": true,
      "$content": true,
      "$definition": true,
      "_id": "page.what-to-do-now--content--26",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Your landlord should not evict you because you asked for repairs to be done \r\n\r\nYour landlord has to keep your home in a good condition and do repairs if you need them. They canâ€™t make you leave your home just for asking for repairs to be done. Your landlord has to follow a proper eviction process if they want you to leave. \r\n\r\nFind out more about this on the [Shelter website](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs/revenge_eviction_if_you_ask_for_repairs).\r\n\r\n### Get free legal help if you are at risk of losing your home\r\n\r\nGovernment funded legal advice and representation (legal aid) is available to people facing possession proceedings. You must have written evidence (for example, an email or a letter) to access support. \r\n\r\nFind out more about [legal aid for possession proceedings](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/legal-aid-for-possession-proceedings).\r\n",
      "show": {
        "identifier": "auto_name__63",
        "operator": "is",
        "value": "auto_value__14"
      }
    },
    {
      "$component": true,
      "$content": true,
      "$definition": true,
      "_id": "page.what-to-do-now--content--27",
      "_type": "content",
      "html": "## Your landlord may not enter your home without notice \r\n\r\nIt is against the law for landlords to enter your home without giving you notice. It is also against the law for them to arrange for anyone else to enter your home, for example builders, without giving you notice. \r\n\r\nFind out more about this on the [Shelter website](https://england.shelter.org.uk/housing_advice/repairs/repairs_and_inspections_access_to_your_rented_home).",
      "show": {
        "identifier": "auto_name__64",
        "operator": "is",
        "value": "auto_value__16"
      }
    },
